<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-AU">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Acknowledgement of Country — Electronic Zoology</title>
<meta name="description" content="Electronic Zoology acknowledges the Wadawurrung People as the Traditional Custodians of the Bellarine Peninsula, on whose Country this work is made.">

<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,300;0,9..144,400;0,9..144,500;0,9..144,600;1,9..144,400&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..60,300;0,8..60,400;0,8..60,500;1,8..60,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

<style>
  :root {
    --paper:      #efe6d4;
    --paper-deep: #e5d9c1;
    --ink:        #1f1a14;
    --ink-soft:   #4a3f32;
    --ochre:      #a0562b;
    --ochre-deep: #7a3f1e;
    --sage:       #5a6b52;
    --rule:       rgba(31, 26, 20, 0.18);
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  body {
    font-family: 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink);
    background-color: var(--paper);
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at top left, rgba(160, 86, 43, 0.06), transparent 50%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom right, rgba(90, 107, 82, 0.08), transparent 50%);
    min-height: 100vh;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
  }


  main {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem 1.75rem 6rem;
  }

  .site-header {
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    background: #1f1a14;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    height: 60px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
  }
  .site-header .site-name {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #efe6d4;
    text-decoration: none;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .site-header .site-name span { color: #a0562b; }
  .site-header .site-name small {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #7a6050;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .site-header nav a {
    color: #c8b99a;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .site-header nav a:hover { color: #a0562b; }
  .site-header nav a.cookie-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #7a3f1e;
    color: #efe6d4 !important;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.52rem;
    padding: 0.08rem 0.3rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    transform: rotate(-7deg);
    transition: transform 0.15s, opacity 0.15s;
  }
  .site-header nav a.cookie-btn:hover { opacity: 0.9; transform: rotate(0deg); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .site-header {
      height: auto;
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .site-header nav { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.25rem 0; }
    .site-header nav a { margin-left: 0; margin-right: 1rem; font-size: 0.85rem; }
  }

  header h1 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144;
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 3.8rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  header h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ochre-deep);
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .acknowledgement {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 3vw, 1.7rem);
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--ink);
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    margin: 2rem 0 3.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    position: relative;
  }

  .acknowledgement::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: -1px;
    left: 0;
    width: 3rem;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--ochre);
  }

  .acknowledgement p + p { margin-top: 1.25rem; }

  .acknowledgement strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ochre-deep);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  section h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.24em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--sage);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  section p + p { margin-top: 1rem; }

  section p {
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .lang {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ochre-deep);
  }

  .resources {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .resources li {
    padding: 0.9rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--rule);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }

  .resources li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .resources a {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ochre);
    display: inline-block;
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    align-self: flex-start;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .resources a:hover { color: var(--ochre-deep); border-bottom-color: var(--ochre-deep); }

  .resources small {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .refrain {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2.5rem 1rem;
  }

  .refrain p {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--ochre-deep);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .au-map {
    position: absolute;
    top: 2rem;
    right: 2rem;
    width: 135px;
    opacity: 0.18;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .au-map img { width: 100%; height: auto; transform: rotate(15deg); }

  .refrain .dingbat {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    color: var(--ochre);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.5em;
    padding-left: 0.5em;
  }

  footer {
    margin-top: 5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    text-align: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    main { padding: 3rem 1.25rem 4rem; }
    .eyebrow { font-size: 0.7rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
    .acknowledgement { padding: 2rem 0; margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="site-header">
  <a class="site-name" href="/">Electronic<span>Zoology</span><small>field notes from the garage</small></a>
  <nav>
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <a href="/guides">Guides</a>
    <a href="/projects">Projects</a>
    <a href="/origin">Origins</a>
  </nav>
</header>

<main>


  <div class="au-map" aria-hidden="true">
    <img src="/images/australia_outline_dark.png" alt="">
  </div>

<header>
    <h1>Acknowledgement of <em>Country</em></h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A note from the garage, on Wadawurrung land.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="acknowledgement">
    <p>
      Electronic Zoology is made on the lands of the
      <strong>Wadawurrung People</strong>, the Traditional Custodians of the
      Bellarine Peninsula, its waterways and its skies.
    </p>
    <p>
      I acknowledge their Elders past and present, and pay my respects to all
      Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples who read this. I acknowledge that sovereignty
      was never ceded.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2>Where this is written</h2>
    <p>
      The garage sits on <span class="lang">Bellawiyn</span> &mdash; the
      Wadawurrung name for the Bellarine Peninsula, meaning
      <em>place of resting by the fire</em>. Wadawurrung Country stretches from
      the coast at Aireys Inlet, around the Bellarine and up through Djilang
      (Geelong) to Ballarat and the Great Dividing Range. It is one of the five
      nations of the Kulin.
    </p>
    <p>
      These lands, waters and skies have been cared for across thousands of
      generations. The middens, songlines, scar trees and gathering places of
      the Bellarine are not relics; they are living culture. Wadawurrung People
      are still here, still caring for Country.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why this matters to a maker</h2>
    <p>
      Everything built in this garage &mdash; the circuits, the prints, the
      salvaged screens, the code &mdash; draws on the materials and quiet of
      this place. The workbench sits on soil that has held story, law and
      craft for tens of thousands of years before a soldering iron was ever
      switched on here.
    </p>
    <p>
      Acknowledging that is the smallest thing I can do. Listening, reading,
      and supporting Wadawurrung-led work is the rest.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Further reading &amp; support</h2>
    <ul class="resources">
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.wadawurrung.org.au/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wadawurrung Traditional Owners Aboriginal Corporation</a>
        <small>The Registered Aboriginal Party for Wadawurrung Country.</small>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://www.wadawurrung.org.au/country-plan" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Paleert Tjaara Dja — Wadawurrung Country Plan</a>
        <small>Let&rsquo;s make Country good together, 2020&ndash;2030.</small>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://aiatsis.gov.au/explore/map-indigenous-australia" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AIATSIS Map of Indigenous Australia</a>
        <small>Find whose Country you&rsquo;re on, wherever you are.</small>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <div class="refrain">
    <span class="dingbat">&mdash; &mdash; &mdash;</span>
    <p>Always was, always will be Aboriginal land.</p>
  </div>

  <footer>
    Electronic Zoology &middot; The Tech-ologist &middot; St Leonards, Victoria (Bellawiyn Country)
  </footer>

</main>

</body>
</html>
